# Design-phase documentation

All design phases that use a Cursor plan must be documented.

## Location

Everything lives under `./documentation/`:
- **Meta-docs**: `INDEX.md`, `LIFECYCLE.md`
- **By type**: subfolders `adr/`, `wa/`, `ost/`, `prd/`

## Document types

| Type | Folder | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| **ADR** | `documentation/adr/` | Technical decisions |
| **WA** | `documentation/wa/` | Working agreements, project management |
| **OST** | `documentation/ost/` | Exploration of future features |
| **PRD** | `documentation/prd/` | Already shipped features |

## Naming convention

- `ADR{number}-{short-description}.md` (e.g. `ADR001-babylonjs-choice.md`)
- `WA{number}-{short-description}.md` (e.g. `WA001-code-review.md`)
- `OST{number}-{short-description}.md` (e.g. `OST001-multiplayer-system.md`)
- `PRD{number}-{short-description}.md` (e.g. `PRD001-character-movement.md`)

Sequential numbering per type. Update `documentation/INDEX.md` for each new document.
